Freddie substrate gotchas batch 3: (1) freddie exec command Windows invocation — plugins/core-cli/plugin.js registers exec for non-interactive scripted use. Correct on Windows: "bun run bin/freddie.js exec --prompt '...'". Do NOT use "bun x freddie" — hangs on Windows due to npm registry fetch timeouts. Args: --prompt (required), --model (default ''), --timeout (default 60000ms). Validated entry point for CI pipelines. (2) acptoapi-bridge max_tokens silent truncation: src/agent/acptoapi-bridge.js line 20 controls max_tokens. Prior to commit e5fb1b7 was 1024, silently truncated. Raised to 4096. If generation output incomplete, verify max_tokens>=4096. (3) GitHub Actions deploy-pages@v5 duplicate artifact rejection — rejects if 2+ artifacts named "github-pages". Fix: trigger fresh run via empty commit instead of "gh run rerun --failed". (4) Rebase regression trap ROOT FIX (2026-05-04): restore-package.cjs now does "npm view anentrypoint-design version" and pins ^<latest>; publish.yml runs "npm install --package-lock-only". Recurrence tell: if pages CI fails with "lock file's anentrypoint-design@X.Y.Z does not satisfy", audit restore-package.cjs and publish.yml for reversion.